casebody.data:
In re T.M.

[Cite as In re T.M., 119 Ohio St.3d 1205, 2008-Ohio-3822.]

*1206(No. 2007-2317 Submitted June 24, 2008 Decided August 5, 2008.) Stephen J. Pronai, Madison County Prosecuting Attorney, and Rachel M. Price, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee, Madison County Department of Job and Family Services. Renae E. Zabloudil, for appellants, Summer Overfield and Shane Manley. Stephen K. Haller, Greene County Prosecuting Attorney, and Stephanie R. Hayden, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, urging affirmance for amicus curiae, Ohio Prosecuting Attorneys Association. Timothy Young, Ohio Public Defender, and Melissa M. Prendergast, Assistant Ohio Public Defender, urging reversal for amicus curiae, Ohio Public Defender.

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently accepted.

Moyer, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Connor, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, and Cupp, JJ., concur.
